g.text: If we want to send messages to multiple SQS queue, but you send them individually to every SQS queue then there can be problems if application fails or any other issue occurs.
To prevent this we use Fan Out pattern.
- SNS (Simple Notification Service) sends a message to multiple destinations.
- SQS (Simple Queue Service) queues receives the same message from SNS.
Push once in SNS, receive in all SQS queues that are subscribers.
* SQS allows data persistence, delayed processing and retries.
* Ability to add more SQS subscribers.
* Make sure your SQS queue access policy allows for SNS to write.
